              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate a prorated value based on a given date range. This function is typically used in financial or subscription-based applications where costs or values need to be allocated proportionally over a specific period."
